Authenticity Lab Frameworks

VOICE

Volume, Origin, Intent, Content, Emotion. Students decode audience conversations and map brand perception in real time using social listening data. Connects to PACT interaction layer cues.

Centaur vs Cyborg

When to partition tasks between human and AI versus when to fuse them. Students design and test both allocation models against trust thresholds from the Threshold Model research.

End to end campaign architecture with AI augmentation at each stage. Students evaluate synthetic content at every gate using ontological pulse and narrative stitching diagnostics.

Research

Synthetic Authenticity in AI Mediated Markets

My doctoral research investigates how audiences construct authenticity judgments for artificial communicators. The core finding is counterintuitive. Synthetic entities do not need to accumulate authenticity cues the way humans do. They optimize for sufficiency, being real enough, rather than richness. When that threshold is crossed, audiences shift from communication to forensic audit. This insight has direct implications for how brands design AI personas, disclose synthetic content, and build trust in automated markets.

Field Observations

Core Frameworks

PACT

Perceived Authenticity Cue Taxonomy. 11 cue families mapped across source, message, and interaction layers. The field’s first unified map of how audiences judge whether a communicator is real.

128 papers coded · κ = 0.73

PAAP

Perceived Authenticity of AI Personas. Models how synthetic communicators achieve perceived authenticity through channel sufficiency, script selectivity, and relational boundaries. Six falsifiable propositions.

111 AI persona studies · PRISMA guided · κ = 0.79

Threshold Model

Synthetic communicators optimize for real enough sufficiency, not cue rich realism. Cross the threshold, and audiences shift from communication to forensic audit. The line between trusted AI and detected AI.

Ontological load · Sufficiency vs realism

IC DT RT Triad

Information Credibility, Disclosure Transparency, and Reputation Trust. The parsimonious three variable diagnostic that recurs across every layer of AI persona evaluation.

Cross layer authenticity diagnostic

Transparency Tax

Disclosure does not kill engagement. 78% of the apparent gap comes from narrative content displacement, not audience rejection of synthetic identity. The cost of honesty is misattributed.

2,531 posts · IRR 1.087 · p=.014

Synthetic Authenticity Mechanisms

Ontological pulse, narrative stitching, and effortful reciprocity. The three field mechanisms by which AI influencers construct perceived authenticity without deceiving audiences.

Study 3 · Field mechanisms
